Create an iOS app named "BioLoop" - a health analytics platform.
TECHNICAL SETUP:

iOS 16.0+ minimum deployment
Swift 5.9+ with TypeScript strict mode for business logic
MVVM architecture with Combine framework
Tab bar navigation with 4 tabs: Home, Activity, Biology, Profile

HEALTHKIT INTEGRATION:
Request read permissions for these exact data types:

Heart rate samples (HKQuantityType.heartRate)
Resting heart rate (HKQuantityType.restingHeartRate)
Heart rate variability SDNN (HKQuantityType.heartRateVariabilitySDNN)
VO2 max (HKQuantityType.vo2Max)
Workout type (HKWorkoutType)
Sleep analysis (HKCategoryType.sleepAnalysis)
Body mass (HKQuantityType.bodyMass)
Height (HKQuantityType.height)
Date of birth (HKCharacteristicType.dateOfBirth)

Add Info.plist key:
NSHealthShareUsageDescription: "BioLoop analyzes your heart rate, HRV, sleep, and workout data to calculate your Performance Index and biological age. Your data never leaves your device."
DATA MODELS:
typescriptinterface UserProfile {
  id: string;
  dateOfBirth: Date;
  height: number; // cm
  onboardingComplete: boolean;
  createdAt: Date;
}

interface DailyMetrics {
  date: Date;
  restingHR?: number;
  hrv?: number;
  vo2max?: number;
  sleepDuration?: number;
  sleepConsistency?: number;
  bodyMass?: number;
  workouts: WorkoutSession[];
  computedAt: Date;
}

interface WorkoutSession {
  startTime: Date;
  duration: number;
  averageHR: number;
  peakHR: number;
  hrAfter60s?: number;
  type: string;
}
STORAGE:

Use Core Data with AES-256 encryption
Entity names: UserProfile, DailyMetrics, WorkoutSession, Baselines
No iCloud sync
Local device only

ERROR HANDLING:
All HealthKit queries must be wrapped in try/catch:
swiftfunc fetchHealthData() async throws -> DailyMetrics {
  do {
    let authorized = try await requestAuthorization()
    guard authorized else { 
      throw HealthKitError.unauthorized 
    }
    let data = try await queryData()
    return validateData(data)
  } catch {
    print("HealthKit error: \(error)")
    throw error
  }
}
Create a HealthKitManager class with:

requestAuthorization() method
fetchDailyMetrics(for date: Date) method
Defensive programming: check for nil, NaN, Infinity
Return default values on error, never crash

TAB BAR:

Tab 1: Home icon 🏠, title "Home"
Tab 2: Activity icon 📊, title "Activity"
Tab 3: Biology icon 🧬, title "Biology"
Tab 4: Profile icon ⚙️, title "Profile"

Use SF Symbols: house.fill, chart.bar.fill, heart.text.square.fill, person.fill
DESIGN SYSTEM:
Primary color: #0066FF (blue)
Background: System background
Cards: Rounded corners 16pt, shadow
Typography: San Francisco (system font)
Large titles: 34pt bold
Body: 17pt regular
